        <div class="expandable-div" id="div-1">
            <div class="header">
                <h5 class="titleFont">Description of Benchmark</h5>
                <button class="btn btn-sm" onclick="toggleContent(1)" id="button-1">+</button>
            </div>
            <div class="content">
                <p><strong>EvidenceBench</strong> is a benchmark designed to evaluate models' ability to retrieve evidence from biomedical literature. It includes over 400 annotated biomedical papers with approximately 700,000 sentence-level annotations, each identifying relevant study aspects that provide evidence for or against scientific hypotheses.</p>

                <p><strong>Key Components:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Datasets</strong>: Expert-annotated biomedical papers with detailed study aspects.</li>
                    <li><strong>Tasks</strong>: Evidence Retrieval @K (ER@K), where models retrieve sentences that best cover the study aspects.</li>
                    <li><strong>Evaluation Metrics</strong>: Aspect Recall @K, measuring the fraction of study aspects covered by the retrieved sentences.</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>Evaluation Strategies:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Chain-of-Thought Prompting</strong>: Guides models through logical reasoning steps.</li>
                    <li><strong>In-Context Learning (ICL)</strong>: Uses example-based prompting to enhance understanding.</li>
                    <li><strong>Section-by-Section Processing</strong>: Retrieves evidence from each section of a paper independently.</li>
                    <li><strong>Instruction-following Embedding Systems</strong>: Utilizes advanced embedding models to optimize retrieval.</li>
                </ul>

                <p>EvidenceBench provides a comprehensive and standardized framework for testing and improving evidence retrieval models, fostering innovation in biomedical information processing.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="expandable-div" id="div-2">
            <div class="header">
                <h5 class="titleFont">Evaluation Metrics</h5>
                <button class="btn btn-sm" onclick="toggleContent(2)" id="button-2">+</button>
            </div>
            <div class="content">
                <p><strong>Evaluation Metrics:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p><strong>Aspect Recall @K</strong></p>
                        <p>Aspect Recall @K measures the fraction of study aspects covered by a set of K retrieved sentences. Let {s1, …, sk} be the set of retrieved sentences and {f1, …, fm} be the set of study aspects in the evidence set. Aspect Recall @K is defined as:</p>
                        <pre>
Aspect Recall @K = (Σ 1(if Σ S(si, fj) ≥ 1)) / m
                        </pre>
                        <p>This metric evaluates how well the retrieved sentences cover the relevant study aspects. It is crucial for determining the effectiveness of evidence retrieval systems in covering important aspects of a study.</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>Task Definitions:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p><strong>Evidence Retrieval @Optimal (ER @optimal)</strong></p>
                        <p><strong>Description:</strong> Retrieve the smallest number of sentences needed to cover all study aspects.</p>
                        <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Form the best evidence set for or against a hypothesis with no more than the optimal number of sentences.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p><strong>Evidence Retrieval @10 (ER @10)</strong></p>
                        <p><strong>Description:</strong> Retrieve no more than 10 sentences to provide evidence for or against a hypothesis.</p>
                        <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Achieve a maximum possible performance with a limited number of sentences.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p><strong>Result Evidence Retrieval @Optimal (Result ER @Optimal)</strong></p>
                        <p><strong>Description:</strong> Retrieve the optimal number of sentences covering study aspects labeled as “Results”.</p>
                        <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Focus on retrieving sentences related to results only.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p><strong>Result Evidence Retrieval @5 (Result ER @5)</strong></p>
                        <p><strong>Description:</strong> Retrieve no more than 5 sentences related to results.</p>
                        <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Provide targeted evaluation with a limited number of sentences.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p><strong>Result Evidence Retrieval Unconstrained (Result ER Unconstrained)</strong></p>
                        <p><strong>Description:</strong> Retrieve any number of sentences deemed necessary.</p>
                        <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Maximize coverage without a sentence limit.</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

